commit.message: Fix package.use parsing of "::repo" package atom specification.
bump release
Ignore hidden files
Update portpeek for 3.2.2
Update copyright date
Fix */* error, see bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/740120
Fix bug in is_any_cpv_file_masked
Update copyright year
Fix incorrect package masking logic

Add support for notifying when a duplicate use flag is
in package.use/* and make.conf

Support package.env

Added support for the analysis of the package.env files
Updated man page
bump version
Add missing declarations
Performance optimizations

If the 't' (check tilde) option is not selected,
do not try to intepret the line

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/693670
Add tilde option to --help command

Fixed incorrect options in both the man page and the code itself.
Thanks to Bruce Guenter for reportiong. See Gentoo bug #686582
Fix portage api call from using deprecated parameters
Handle wildcard entries for useflags when no package in category is installed. See bug #646520
Ignore python USE_EXPAND variables
Recognize USE_EXPAND in package.use. See bug #615998. Thanks to Erik Quaeghebeur for reporting. Do not remove blank lines from package.use/*
Stop removing blank lines. Fixes bug #610734
Removed unneeded code. Bump version for next release.
Fix for bug #606092, thanks to Derk for reporting and BobbyK for the analysis
Fix debug logging
Handle unreadable files. Work on bug when parsing package.use files. Bug #601446
Fix for =category/package-version* (asterick handling)
Make sure package even exists before seeing if it's installed.
